    Still sounds good after 6 years

Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2020Style: GXL2200Verified Purchase









    I bought this mic about 6 years ago and will still use it from time to time. It has been tossed about quite a bit and has held up excellently. The sound is neutral with great clarity and I prefer it over some more expensive mics for percussion (room mic or things like bongos or shakers). It sounds good for vocals and guitar as well, but I have more expensive mics that I prefer for those tasks. However, if you can only have one mic, you really can't go wrong with this for the price. Being a large diaphragm cardioid it will pick up lots of background noise, so if you work in a noisy environment this may not be the mic for you.  Also be aware of squeaking chairs and other room noise, because you can be sure those will be picked up with this mic as well!

